<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-12-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-12-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="436" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d436">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Carter</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-12-18"><hi rend="italic">December 18,
                                    1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Carter conveys the thanks of Sir Edward Grey for the prompt action
                            of the Department in regard to the matter reported in his telegram of
                            the 16th instant. Equal prompt consideration will be given to
                            Department’s recommendation regarding the cutting of nets.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>